HEADWORD: Kingbolt
<hw>King"bolt`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A vertical iron
bolt, by which the forward axle and wheels of a vehicle or the trucks of
a railroad car are connected with the other parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>King Charles spaniel</ent>⟦br⟧
